---
// Phase 2 Cluster 4 #3 — Wine Enthusiast wine cooler pillar.
// Brand: Wine Enthusiast Companies, NY, founded 1979. Started as wine
// accessories catalog, expanded к wine coolers. Dual-tier reality:
// Silent Series (thermoelectric) + Classic Wood Series + VinoView (premium
// $1500-3000) PLUS entry-tier mass-market disposable. Honest tier split.
// Critical technical angle: Silent Series uses thermoelectric Peltier
// modules (no compressor) — different repair approach than typical
// compressor wine coolers.
// Residential pricing ($89). NEW schema pattern via mergeCredentials().

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { mergeCredentials } from '../../data/credentials-schema';

const phone = '(323) 870-4790';
const phoneRaw = phone.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/wine-enthusiast-wine-cooler/";

const title = "Wine Enthusiast Wine Cooler Repair LA — Same Day";
const description = "Wine Enthusiast wine cooler repair across LA. Silent Series thermoelectric, Classic Wood, VinoView. Premium tier vs entry-tier honest split. EPA 608, $89 dx.";

const faqs = [
  { q: "Is my Wine Enthusiast cooler the premium tier или the entry-tier?", a: "Critical question, и the answer changes the repair-vs-replace math significantly. Silent Series (thermoelectric quiet operation, $800-1800 retail), Classic Wood Series (premium hardwood-front cabinets, $1500-3000 retail), и VinoView Series (luxury display configurations, $1200-2500 retail) are the premium tier — repair almost always makes sense, even на 8+ year-old units. Entry-tier Wine Enthusiast wine coolers ($300-500 retail, often distributed through warehouse clubs или Amazon) — replacement usually wins the math, even на repairs under $200, because the unit's remaining service life expectancy is short. We identify your specific Series during the diagnostic by model number и frame the math honestly before you commit к anything. The brand markets itself как single tier; the underlying reality is two-tier с very different service equations." },
  { q: "How does Silent Series repair differ from typical wine coolers?", a: "Silent Series uses thermoelectric Peltier module cooling instead of conventional compressor refrigeration. No compressor, no refrigerant, no EPA 608 work — entirely different system. The Peltier modules are solid-state heat pumps that move heat from inside the cabinet к outside через the temperature differential. Failure modes are different: Peltier module degradation over 10+ years, heat-sink fan motor wear, controller board fade. The diagnostic approach is electrical и thermal rather than refrigeration. Service life of Silent Series typically 10-15 years; replacement Peltier modules and fan assemblies are sourceable through Wine Enthusiast parts. The trade-off is quiet operation (no compressor noise — Silent Series is genuinely quiet) at the cost of thermal capacity (works best with smaller cabinets и moderate ambient temperature)." },
  { q: "Same-day Wine Enthusiast service in LA?", a: "Yes for diagnostic and most common repairs. Most calls received before 2 PM get a tech on-site the same business day. Common service items — door gaskets, condenser fan motors (compressor units), Peltier modules and heat-sink fans (Silent Series), control boards, и cabinet door seals — typically ride on the truck for premium-tier configurations. Less common items may add 1-5 business days for parts ordering through Wine Enthusiast parts distribution." },
  { q: "Do you carry Wine Enthusiast OEM parts on the truck?", a: "Common service parts for premium-tier units ride on every wine cooler truck: door gaskets in standard configurations, evaporator and condenser fan motors for compressor models, common control board components, и Peltier module replacements for Silent Series. Premium-specific items — Classic Wood Series cabinet hardware, VinoView display configurations parts — come through Wine Enthusiast parts distribution, typically 1-7 business days. Entry-tier mass-market parts: typically not stocked because we don't recommend repair on those units anyway (replacement math wins). We confirm availability before scheduling labor." },
  { q: "What's your diagnostic fee for Wine Enthusiast?", a: "$89 residential diagnostic, waived when you approve the repair. The diagnostic covers tier identification (Silent / Classic Wood / VinoView / entry-tier), full system assessment (refrigerant work under EPA 608 for compressor models, electrical/thermal for Silent Series), door seal integrity, exterior cabinet condition, и a written quote with parts cost, labor estimate, и realistic timeline before any work begins. Tier identification is the first step и shapes everything else." },
  { q: "Is Classic Wood Series worth the premium over standard wine coolers?", a: "For aesthetic value, yes — Classic Wood Series cabinets are real hardwood с premium finishes, and the build quality reads as furniture rather than appliance. The cabinet itself is durable and outlasts the cooling unit inside (similar к Le Cache cabinet philosophy). For service value: Classic Wood is repairable as a cabinet (door alignment, gasket replacement, finish maintenance) и serviceable как cooling system (compressor, fan motors, control board). The combined service-life expectation runs 12-18 years с maintenance — meaningfully longer than entry-tier alternatives. Repair value math typically favors repair on Classic Wood units under 12 years old. Past that, depending на extent of failure и cabinet condition, replacement consideration begins." }
];

const localBusinessSchema = mergeCredentials({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'HomeAndConstructionBusiness', '@id': canonical + '#business',
  name: 'Same Day Appliance Repair — Wine Enthusiast Wine Cooler Service',
  url: canonical, telephone: phone, email: 'support@samedayappliance.repair', priceRange: '$$',
  openingHoursSpecification: [
    { '@type': 'OpeningHoursSpecification', dayOfWeek: ['Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday'], opens: '08:00', closes: '20:00' },
    { '@type': 'OpeningHoursSpecification', dayOfWeek: 'Sunday', opens: '00:00', closes: '00:00' }
  ],
  areaServed: [
    { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Los Angeles County' }, { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Orange County' },
    { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Ventura County' }, { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'San Bernardino County' },
    { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Riverside County' }
  ]
});

const serviceSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'Service', '@id': canonical + '#service',
  serviceType: 'Wine Enthusiast Wine Cooler Repair',
  name: 'Wine Enthusiast Wine Cooler Repair, Same Day Appliance Repair',
  url: canonical,
  description: 'Same-day Wine Enthusiast wine cooler repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Silent Series (thermoelectric Peltier), Classic Wood Series (premium hardwood cabinets), VinoView Series (luxury display), and entry-tier consumer line. Honest tier-identification и repair-vs-replace math during diagnostic. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410), BHGS #A49573, CSLB C-20 HVAC. $89 residential diagnostic, applied toward repair.',
  provider: { '@id': canonical + '#business' },
  areaServed: [
    { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Los Angeles County' }, { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Orange County' },
    { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Ventura County' }, { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'San Bernardino County' },
    { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Riverside County' }
  ],
  brand: { '@type': 'Brand', name: 'Wine Enthusiast', sameAs: 'https://www.wineenthusiast.com/' },
  offers: { '@type': 'Offer', priceSpecification: { '@type': 'PriceSpecification', price: '89.00', priceCurrency: 'USD', description: 'Residential diagnostic fee, applied toward repair' } }
};

const faqSchema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faqs.map(f => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) };
const breadcrumbSchema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
  { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://samedayappliance.repair/' },
  { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Brands', item: 'https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/' },
  { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'Wine Enthusiast', item: canonical }
]};
const schemaJsons = [localBusinessSchema, serviceSchema, faqSchema, breadcrumbSchema];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<ServiceHero
  eyebrow="Wine Cooler · Premium + Mass-Market Dual Tier"
  title="Wine Enthusiast Wine Cooler Repair, Across Southern California"
  subtitle="Silent Series thermoelectric · Classic Wood Series premium hardwood · VinoView luxury display, plus entry-tier consumer. Honest tier identification и repair-vs-replace math during diagnostic. EPA 608 Universal certified, BHGS #A49573. $89 residential diagnostic, waived with repair."
  heroImageTitle="Wine Enthusiast Wine Cooler Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2>The dual-tier wine cooler brand с distinct service equations</h2>
    <p>
      Wine Enthusiast Companies started в 1979 as a wine accessories catalog — corkscrews, decanters, glassware, storage
      accessories — и evolved into a wine cooler manufacturer over the following decades. The brand carries a unique
      structural reality в the wine cooler category: it operates simultaneously at two distinct tiers с very different
      service value equations. Premium-tier offerings (Silent Series thermoelectric, Classic Wood Series premium hardwood,
      VinoView Series luxury display) compete с serious wine cooler brands в the $1500-3000 retail range и serve serious
      Beverly Hills и Bel Air wine collectors. Entry-tier mass-market offerings ($300-500 retail) compete с warehouse-club
      и Amazon wine coolers. The brand markets itself as a single Wine Enthusiast experience; the service reality is two
      different conversations.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pricing structure: $89 residential diagnostic, waived when you approve the repair. EPA 608 Universal certified для
      refrigerant work on compressor models, BHGS Registration #A49573, CSLB C-20 HVAC. The first thing we do during the
      diagnostic is identify which tier и which series your specific Wine Enthusiast unit is — that determines the
      repair-vs-replace math и the entire service approach.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02, Series and product coverage</p>
    <h2>What we service across the Wine Enthusiast lineup</h2>

    <h3>Silent Series — thermoelectric premium</h3>
    <p>
      Wine Enthusiast's thermoelectric line — uses Peltier solid-state heat pumps instead of conventional compressor
      refrigeration. No compressor, no refrigerant. The trade-off is genuinely quiet operation (the brand name accurately
      describes the experience — Silent Series is the quietest wine cooler в most LA homes) at the cost of thermal capacity
      (works best с smaller cabinets и moderate ambient temperature). Service approach is electrical и thermal — Peltier
      module diagnostics, heat-sink fan motor service, controller board work. Different parts catalog than compressor models.
      Service life typically 10-15 years с good operating environment.
    </p>

    <h3>Classic Wood Series — premium hardwood cabinets</h3>
    <p>
      Real hardwood cabinetry — cherry, walnut, oak depending on the specific model — built к look like furniture rather
      than appliance. Common в LA dining rooms, home libraries, и open-plan kitchen integrations where the wine cooler
      doubles as a furniture piece. Capacity varies by configuration; typical range 30-150 bottles. The cabinet itself is
      durable и outlasts the cooling unit inside (similar к Le Cache philosophy). Service items include cabinet hardware
      (hinges, latches, finish protection during access), gasket replacement, и cooling system service (compressor, fan
      motors, control board). Combined service life expectation 12-18 years с maintenance.
    </p>

    <h3>VinoView Series — luxury display</h3>
    <p>
      Wine Enthusiast's luxury display configurations — large glass front doors, premium lighting, и often specialty shelving
      designed к showcase the wine collection visually. Common в design-forward homes и high-end residential wine bars.
      Capacity varies. Service approach is conventional wine cooler diagnostic с extra care на the glass-front display
      panel и premium lighting components.
    </p>

    <h3>Entry-tier consumer wine coolers</h3>
    <p>
      Mass-market line — distributed through warehouse clubs, Amazon, и big-box retail. Build quality matches the price
      point ($300-500 retail). We service these но frame the repair-vs-replace math honestly during the diagnostic — for
      entry-tier units, replacement usually wins the math decision over significant repair costs because remaining service
      life expectancy is short и the unit's residual value low. The fairest approach is к identify the tier first и tell the
      customer what they have before they commit к parts cost.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03, Common failure patterns</p>
    <h2>What we look at first on a Wine Enthusiast call</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Tier identification — first step, every time.</strong> Silent Series, Classic Wood, VinoView, или entry-tier? The diagnostic identifies this by model number и serial-plate verification before anything else, because the service approach diverges meaningfully между tiers и technologies (thermoelectric vs compressor).</li>
      <li><strong>Silent Series — Peltier module degradation after 10+ years.</strong> Thermoelectric cooling efficiency reduces gradually as Peltier modules age. Symptom is cabinet temperature drift — unit can't quite hold setpoint, especially in warmer ambient conditions. Diagnostic is electrical и thermal rather than refrigeration. Replacement Peltier modules sourced through Wine Enthusiast parts.</li>
      <li><strong>Silent Series — heat-sink fan motor wear.</strong> The fan motor moving air across the heat-sink на the warm side of the Peltier module wears with use. Symptom is similar к Peltier degradation but distinguishable on diagnostic. Replacement motors stocked для common configurations.</li>
      <li><strong>Classic Wood + VinoView (compressor models) — condenser fouling.</strong> LA dust environment fous condensers at typical 6-8 week intervals на units in busy kitchens or dining rooms. Symptom is unit running constantly with warm cabinet. About 30% of "not cooling" calls на these series resolve at condenser cleaning, no parts needed.</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket compression set after 5-7 years.</strong> Common across all tiers. Symptom is icing на the evaporator from moisture infiltration или unit struggling к hold setpoint. Replacement gaskets stocked для common configurations across Silent / Classic Wood / VinoView Series.</li>
      <li><strong>Control board fade after 8-12 years.</strong> Newer units с digital displays и electronic temperature controls show capacitor aging. Symptom is intermittent display issues или setpoint drift. Diagnostic confirms before swap; we don't replace control boards on suspicion.</li>
      <li><strong>Cabinet door alignment drift on Classic Wood.</strong> Heavy hardwood doors cycle thousands of times over the life of the cabinet и hinges develop play. Symptom is door not closing cleanly к gasket, leading к seal failure. Hinge adjustment or replacement restores alignment.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04, Where we work most on Wine Enthusiast</p>
    <h2>The LA Wine Enthusiast footprint our techs know best</h2>
    <p><strong>Beverly Hills wine collector homes — premium tier deployments.</strong> Silent Series, Classic Wood Series, и VinoView Series в serious residential wine collector homes. The serious collectors who chose Wine Enthusiast specifically для quiet operation (Silent Series) или для cabinet aesthetics (Classic Wood, VinoView). Service approach standard residential — careful access, surrounding architecture protection, customer-specific scheduling.</p>
    <p><strong>Bel Air и Pacific Palisades home libraries и dining rooms.</strong> Classic Wood Series и VinoView в design-forward home builds where the wine cooler is part of the room aesthetic. Service work respects the surrounding furnishings.</p>
    <p><strong>Hollywood Hills и Studio City modern homes — Silent Series в kitchen integrations.</strong> Silent Series's quiet operation is valued в open-plan kitchen и living designs where compressor noise would be objectionable. Common LA market segment.</p>
    <p><strong>Entry-tier mass-market deployments across all LA areas.</strong> Apartment kitchens, smaller condo installations, secondary residences. Honest framing на repair-vs-replace math; we don't waste customer money pushing repairs on disposable units.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2>What this month looked like on Wine Enthusiast</h2>
    <div class="repair-cards">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <p class="repair-quote">"Silent Series getting warmer over time, can't hold cellar temp anymore."</p>
        <p>Beverly Hills home, Silent Series thermoelectric wine cooler, install year per the homeowner approximately 2014. Diagnostic confirmed Peltier module degradation — cooling output measurably reduced from spec на load test. Sourced replacement Peltier modules and heat-sink fan assembly through Wine Enthusiast parts distribution (5 business days). Returned для install on second visit, replaced affected modules, calibrated thermal output, ran cabinet pull-down test for two hours. The homeowner specifically chose Silent Series для the quiet operation в open-plan living area — repair restored the original quiet operation plus full cooling capacity.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <p class="repair-quote">"Classic Wood door isn't sealing properly, condensation on the bottom panel."</p>
        <p>Pacific Palisades home, Classic Wood Series freestanding wine cooler в dining room, install year per the homeowner approximately 2017. Diagnostic confirmed two issues: door gasket compression set on the bottom seal (replaceable) и hinge alignment drift (adjustable). Replaced gasket с OEM Wine Enthusiast part, adjusted bottom hinge для proper door-to-gasket contact, verified seal integrity around the full perimeter. The Classic Wood cabinet itself was в excellent condition — homeowner specifically valued the furniture-grade aesthetics, и careful service approach preserved the finish.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <p class="repair-quote">"VinoView display unit stopped cooling, и my visible wine collection is at risk."</p>
        <p>Bel Air home, VinoView Series large glass-front display unit, install year per the homeowner approximately 2018. Diagnostic ran condenser first (heavily fouled — open-plan kitchen environment с visible wine display attracts dust faster than typical wine cooler installations), then verified refrigerant charge (within spec), then re-tested. Coil clean alone dropped cabinet temperature from 65°F к 56°F within two hours. Recommended quarterly cleaning contract (especially relevant для display-style installations); homeowner committed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06, Why us, specifically</p>
    <h2>What makes us a fit for Wine Enthusiast service</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Honest tier identification и repair-vs-replace math.</strong> Silent / Classic Wood / VinoView (premium tier) vs entry-tier — completely different service equations. We identify your unit и frame the math before you commit к anything.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermoelectric Silent Series experience.</strong> Different repair approach than compressor wine coolers — Peltier module diagnostics, heat-sink fan service, controller work. Many appliance shops don't service thermoelectric wine coolers; we do.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608 Universal certification (#1346255700410).</strong> Required для refrigerant work on Classic Wood и VinoView (compressor models). Silent Series is electrical-only — no EPA scope, но we have it for the rest of the lineup.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS Registration #A49573 plus CSLB C-20 HVAC.</strong> California state coverage.</li>
      <li><strong>Wine Enthusiast OEM parts only on premium tier.</strong> No aftermarket substitutions on Silent Series Peltier modules, Classic Wood cabinet hardware, or VinoView display components.</li>
      <li><strong>$89 residential diagnostic, waived с repair.</strong> Tier identification is the first thing we do, и we tell the customer the math honestly before any commitment.</li>
      <li><strong>BBB Accredited Business and $1M general liability insured.</strong></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07, Frequently asked questions</p>
    <h2>The questions we get most on Wine Enthusiast calls</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq-item"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p>{f.a}</p></details>))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">08, Other wine cooler brands we cover</p>
    <h2>Wine Enthusiast service в context</h2>
    <ul class="cross-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/eurocave/">EuroCave wine cellars</a> — French luxury alternative</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/le-cache/">Le Cache wine cabinets</a> — American hardwood specialist</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/vinotemp/">Vinotemp wine cooler + cellar</a> — California specialty company</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/summit-wine-cooler/">Summit wine cooler</a> — commercial-grade Felix Storch</li>
      <li><a href="/brands/whisperkool/">WhisperKool wine cellar cooling</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/cellarpro/">CellarPro wine cellar cooling</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/breezaire/">Breezaire wine cellar cooling</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/wine-cooler-repair/">Wine cooler repair (all brands)</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bottom-cta">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <h2>Same-day Wine Enthusiast service across Southern California</h2>
    <p>$89 residential diagnostic, waived with repair. EPA 608 Universal certified, BHGS #A49573, CSLB C-20 HVAC, BBB Accredited.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-red">Call {phone}</a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline">Request service →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); border-top: 1px solid var(--border); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .container.narrow { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-number { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin: 0 0 12px; }
  h2 { font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 32px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; margin: 0 0 20px; color: var(--text); letter-spacing: -.01em; }
  h3 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; margin: 24px 0 10px; color: var(--text); }
  p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin: 0 0 14px; }
  strong { font-weight: 700; }
  a { color: var(--red); text-decoration: none; }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .bullet-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 16px 0; }
  .bullet-list li { position: relative; padding: 12px 0 12px 22px; font-size: 15.5px; line-height: 1.65; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .bullet-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .bullet-list li::before { content: "▸"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; }
  .repair-cards { display: grid; gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .repair-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 26px; }
  .repair-quote { font-style: italic; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 12px; font-size: 15px; }
  .repair-card p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .faq-list { margin-top: 20px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px 0; }
  .faq-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .faq-item summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; color: var(--text); padding: 4px 0; }
  .faq-item summary:hover { color: var(--red); }
  .faq-item p { margin: 12px 0 4px; font-size: 15.5px; color: var(--text); }
  .cross-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 16px 0 0; }
  .cross-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 15px; }
  .cross-links li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 64px 24px; text-align: center; }
  .bottom-cta h2 { color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta p { color: rgba(255,255,255,.85); max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 24px; }
  .bottom-cta a { color: #fff; }
  .cta-row { display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-red { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-outline { border: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,.3); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; }
</style>
